ipadFrPortTable.name: ipadFrPortTable
ipadFrPortTable.description: Table of frame relay port parameters.

ipadFrPortTableEntry.name: ipadFrPortTableEntry
ipadFrPortTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad frame relay port table.

ipadFrPortService.name: ipadFrPortService
ipadFrPortService.description: Index into the ipad frame relay port table; an entry in the ipad service table.

ipadFrPortActive.name: ipadFrPortActive
ipadFrPortActive.description: Specifies if the port is active.

ipadFrPortLMIType.name: ipadFrPortLMIType
ipadFrPortLMIType.description: Specifies the link management information type used on this port.

ipadFrPortLMIMode.name: ipadFrPortLMIMode
ipadFrPortLMIMode.description: Specifies the link management information mode used on this port.

ipadFrPortRxInvAlmThreshold.name: ipadFrPortRxInvAlmThreshold
ipadFrPortRxInvAlmThreshold.description: Sets the rx invalid frames alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadFrPortRxInvAlmAlarm.name: ipadFrPortRxInvAlmAlarm
ipadFrPortRxInvAlmAlarm.description: Reports if the invalid frames threshold has been exceeded.

ipadFrPortTxAlmThreshold.name: ipadFrPortTxAlmThreshold
ipadFrPortTxAlmThreshold.description: Sets the tx throughput alarm threshold (in bits/second). Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadFrPortTxAlmAlarm.name: ipadFrPortTxAlmAlarm
ipadFrPortTxAlmAlarm.description: Reports if the tx throughput threshold has been exceeded.

ipadFrPortRxAlmThreshold.name: ipadFrPortRxAlmThreshold
ipadFrPortRxAlmThreshold.description: Sets the rx throughput alarm threshold (in bits/second). Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadFrPortRxAlmAlarm.name: ipadFrPortRxAlmAlarm
ipadFrPortRxAlmAlarm.description: Reports if the rx throughput threshold has been exceeded.

ipadFrPortAlarmReset.name: ipadFrPortAlarmReset
ipadFrPortAlarmReset.description: This is used to clear the current alarm counts.

ipadServiceTableEntry.name: ipadServiceTableEntry
ipadServiceTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad service table.

ipadServiceIndex.name: ipadServiceIndex
ipadServiceIndex.description: The index for the ipad service table.

ipadServiceifIndex.name: ipadServiceifIndex
ipadServiceifIndex.description: The MIB-II ifIndex for this service.

ipadServicePair.name: ipadServicePair
ipadServicePair.description: An entry in this table, which establishes a service pairing.

ipadServiceStatus.name: ipadServiceStatus
ipadServiceStatus.description: This parameter indicates the status of the service. idle - The service is not doing anything or has not been configured for use. down - The physical layer for the service is not ready. training - The physical layer is not ready but is attempting to come up. connecting - The physical layer is not ready but is attempting to come up. physicalUp - The physical layer is ready the service is not ready. protocolUp - The service is able to pass data. dead - The service is inactive because no resources are available to support it. changed - Service parameters were changed and require a save and restart to take effect.

ipadServiceAddService.name: ipadServiceAddService
ipadServiceAddService.description: Adds a row to the Service Table.

ipadServiceDeleteService.name: ipadServiceDeleteService
ipadServiceDeleteService.description: Identifies a Service to be deleted; an index into the Service Table.

ipadChannelTableEntry.name: ipadChannelTableEntry
ipadChannelTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad channel table.

ipadChannelifIndex.name: ipadChannelifIndex
ipadChannelifIndex.description: Primary index into ipad channel table, MIB-II ifIndex.

ipadChannelIndex.name: ipadChannelIndex
ipadChannelIndex.description: Channel index for the physical interface.

ipadChannelService.name: ipadChannelService
ipadChannelService.description: Index into service table for this channel.

ipadChannelPair.name: ipadChannelPair
ipadChannelPair.description: Pair for this channel; an entry in the channel table. Use service pair in service table to determine which service contains this channel.

ipadDLCITableEntry.name: ipadDLCITableEntry
ipadDLCITableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad DLCI table.

ipadDLCIservice.name: ipadDLCIservice
ipadDLCIservice.description: An index into the ipad service table.

ipadDLCInumber.name: ipadDLCInumber
ipadDLCInumber.description: The DLCI number for this entry.

ipadDLCIactive.name: ipadDLCIactive
ipadDLCIactive.description: Specifies if the DLCI is active.

ipadDLCIcongestion.name: ipadDLCIcongestion
ipadDLCIcongestion.description: Specifies if the dlci is receiving frames with FECN or BECN bit set.

ipadDLCIremoteEquipActive.name: ipadDLCIremoteEquipActive
ipadDLCIremoteEquipActive.description: Reports if the equipment attached to the remote unit is active.

ipadDLCIencapsulation.name: ipadDLCIencapsulation
ipadDLCIencapsulation.description: Type of protocol encapsulation used on this DLCI.

ipadDLCIproprietary.name: ipadDLCIproprietary
ipadDLCIproprietary.description: When the encapsulation is proprietary, the traffic type must be configured to gather protocol specific statistics.

ipadDLCIpropOffset.name: ipadDLCIpropOffset
ipadDLCIpropOffset.description: When the encapsulation is proprietary, this is the number of bytes after the frame relay header to look for the specified protocol decode.

ipadDLCIinBand.name: ipadDLCIinBand
ipadDLCIinBand.description: Determines if frames on this DLCI will be parsed to look for management frames destined for the unit itself.

ipadDLCICIR.name: ipadDLCICIR
ipadDLCICIR.description: Default committed information rate in bits per second.

ipadDLCIBe.name: ipadDLCIBe
ipadDLCIBe.description: Default excess burst rate in bits per second.

ipadDLCIminBC.name: ipadDLCIminBC
ipadDLCIminBC.description: If the corresponding interface is configured to enable congestion management, the minimum transfer rate at which the unit will throttle back offering data to the network.

ipadDLCIrxMon.name: ipadDLCIrxMon
ipadDLCIrxMon.description: Determines if the SLA parameters will be monitored for received frames.

ipadDLCIdEctrl.name: ipadDLCIdEctrl
ipadDLCIdEctrl.description: Determines if the Rx monitor will set the DE bit on all frames received in excess of the CIR before they are switched to their destination port.

ipadDLCItxExCIRThreshold.name: ipadDLCItxExCIRThreshold
ipadDLCItxExCIRThreshold.description: Sets the Tx over CIR alarm threshold. This threshold is the number of bits per second in excess of CIR. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadDLCItxExCIRAlarm.name: ipadDLCItxExCIRAlarm
ipadDLCItxExCIRAlarm.description: Reports if the Tx over CIR threshold has been exceeded.

ipadDLCItxExBeThreshold.name: ipadDLCItxExBeThreshold
ipadDLCItxExBeThreshold.description: Sets the Tx over Be alarm threshold. This threshold is the number of bits per second in excess of Be. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadDLCItxExBeAlarm.name: ipadDLCItxExBeAlarm
ipadDLCItxExBeAlarm.description: Reports if the Tx over Be threshold has been exceeded.

ipadDLCIrxCongThreshold.name: ipadDLCIrxCongThreshold
ipadDLCIrxCongThreshold.description: Sets the Rx congestion alarm threshold. This threshold is the number of frames received with BECN/FECN. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadDLCIrxCongAlarm.name: ipadDLCIrxCongAlarm
ipadDLCIrxCongAlarm.description: Reports if the Rx congestion threshold has been exceeded.

ipadDLCIrxBECNinCIR.name: ipadDLCIrxBECNinCIR
ipadDLCIrxBECNinCIR.description: Reports if BECN has been received within CIR.

ipadDLCIUASThreshold.name: ipadDLCIUASThreshold
ipadDLCIUASThreshold.description: Sets the UAS (unavailable seconds) alarm threshold. This threshold is the number of seconds passed that the DLCI is unavailable. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadDLCIUASAlarm.name: ipadDLCIUASAlarm
ipadDLCIUASAlarm.description: Reports if the UAS threshold has been exceeded.

ipadDLCIAlarmReset.name: ipadDLCIAlarmReset
ipadDLCIAlarmReset.description: This is used to clear the current alarm counts.

ipadDLCIRoundTripDelaySize.name: ipadDLCIRoundTripDelaySize
ipadDLCIRoundTripDelaySize.description: Specifies the packet size in octets used to calculate round trip delay.

ipadDLCIRoundTripDelayRate.name: ipadDLCIRoundTripDelayRate
ipadDLCIRoundTripDelayRate.description: Specifies the packet rate in seconds used to calculate round trip delay.

ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinCIR.name: ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinCIR
ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinCIR.description: Count of frames sent within CIR from the remote end of the DLCI.

ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinBE.name: ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinBE
ipadDLCIRemoteFramesOfferedWithinBE.description: Count of frames sent within BE, but over CIR, from the remote end of the DLCI.

ipadDLCIFramesReceived.name: ipadDLCIFramesReceived
ipadDLCIFramesReceived.description: Count of frames received by the local device on this DLCI.

ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinCIR.name: ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinCIR
ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinCIR.description: Count of data octets sent within CIR from the remote end of the DLCI.

ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinBE.name: ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinBE
ipadDLCIRemoteDataOfferedWithinBE.description: Count of data octets sent within BE, but over CIR, from the remote end of the DLCI.

ipadDLCIDataReceived.name: ipadDLCIDataReceived
ipadDLCIDataReceived.description: Count of data octets received by the local device on this DLCI.

ipadDLCIRemoteIPAddress.name: ipadDLCIRemoteIPAddress
ipadDLCIRemoteIPAddress.description: The IP Address of the device on the remote end of this DLCI. This information is only valid when the remote device supports Verilink's proprietary message exchange.

ipadDLCICompressionStatus.name: ipadDLCICompressionStatus
ipadDLCICompressionStatus.description: This is the current status of the compression engine for this DLCI. disabled(2) indicates that the compression engine is disabled. enabledAndNegotiated(3) indicates that compression is enabled, and has been successfully negotiated with the device at the other end. enabledButNotNegotiated(4) indicated that compression is enabled, but has not been successfully negotiated with the device at the other end. This may be due to the DLCI being down, the other device not having compression enabled or other factors which would inhibit communication.

ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsIn.name: ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsIn
ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsIn.description: This is a rolling counter of the number of octets given to the compression engine.

ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsOut.name: ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsOut
ipadDLCICompressionTxOctetsOut.description: This is a rolling counter of the number of octets output from the compression engine.

ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsIn.name: ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsIn
ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsIn.description: This is a rolling counter of the number of octets given to the compression engine.

ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsOut.name: ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsOut
ipadDLCICompressionRxOctetsOut.description: This is a rolling counter of the number of octets given to the compression engine.

ipadDLCILastChange.name: ipadDLCILastChange
ipadDLCILastChange.description: Time of the last change in the DLCI table.

ipadEndpointTableEntry.name: ipadEndpointTableEntry
ipadEndpointTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad endpoint table.

ipadEndpointIndex.name: ipadEndpointIndex
ipadEndpointIndex.description: The index into the ipad endpoint table.

ipadEndpointService.name: ipadEndpointService
ipadEndpointService.description: An index into the ipad service table.

ipadEndpointDLCInumber.name: ipadEndpointDLCInumber
ipadEndpointDLCInumber.description: Data link connection identifier for this endpoint; The DLCI number for this entry.

ipadEndpointForward.name: ipadEndpointForward
ipadEndpointForward.description: Index into the endpoint names table. This is the endpoint on which data should be forwarded for switched endpoints.

ipadEndpointBackup.name: ipadEndpointBackup
ipadEndpointBackup.description: Index into the endpoint table. This is the endpoint on which data should be forwarded in the case where the endpoint becomes inactive.

ipadEndpointRefSLP.name: ipadEndpointRefSLP
ipadEndpointRefSLP.description: Index into the endpoint table. The service level parameters can be copied from another configured endpoint.

ipadEndpointAddEndpoint.name: ipadEndpointAddEndpoint
ipadEndpointAddEndpoint.description: Identifies an Endpoint to be added.

ipadEndpointDeleteEndpoint.name: ipadEndpointDeleteEndpoint
ipadEndpointDeleteEndpoint.description: Identifies an Endpoint to be deleted.

ipadEndpointLastChange.name: ipadEndpointLastChange
ipadEndpointLastChange.description: Time of the last change in the Endpoint table.

ipadUserTableEntry.name: ipadUserTableEntry
ipadUserTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad user table.

ipadUserIndex.name: ipadUserIndex
ipadUserIndex.description: Index into the ipad user table.

ipadUserFilterByDLCI.name: ipadUserFilterByDLCI
ipadUserFilterByDLCI.description: Enables Service+DLCI filtering for this user statistic.

ipadUserService.name: ipadUserService
ipadUserService.description: Specifies the service for this user type; identifies an entry in the ipad DLCI table when combined with ipadUserDLCI. Meaningful when ipadUserFilterByDLCI is enabled. Meaningless when collecting PPP statistics.

ipadUserDLCI.name: ipadUserDLCI
ipadUserDLCI.description: Specifies the DLCI for this user type; identifies an entry in the ipad DLCI table when combined with ipadUserService. Meaningful when ipadUserFilterByDLCI is enabled. Meaningless when collecting PPP statistics.

ipadUserFilterByIPAddress.name: ipadUserFilterByIPAddress
ipadUserFilterByIPAddress.description: Enables IP address filtering for this user statistic. A packet is counted towards the user statistics if the result of a bitwise-and of an IP address in a transmitted packet with ipadUserIPMask equals ipadUserIPAddress.

ipadUserIPAddress.name: ipadUserIPAddress
ipadUserIPAddress.description: Specifies the IP address for this user type.

ipadUserIPMask.name: ipadUserIPMask
ipadUserIPMask.description: Specifies the IP address mask for this user type.

ipadUserFilterByIPPort.name: ipadUserFilterByIPPort
ipadUserFilterByIPPort.description: Enables IP Port filtering for this user statistic.

ipadUserIPPort.name: ipadUserIPPort
ipadUserIPPort.description: Specifies the IP port for this user type.

ipadUserTxAlmThreshold.name: ipadUserTxAlmThreshold
ipadUserTxAlmThreshold.description: Sets the tx throughput alarm threshold in bits per second. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm.

ipadUserTxAlmAlarm.name: ipadUserTxAlmAlarm
ipadUserTxAlmAlarm.description: Reports if the tx throughput threshold has been exceeded.

ipadUserAlarmReset.name: ipadUserAlarmReset
ipadUserAlarmReset.description: This is used to clear the current alarm counts.

ipadUserVpi.name: ipadUserVpi
ipadUserVpi.description: Specifies the Vpi for this user type; identifies a VC when combined with the ipadUserService and ipadUserVci objects. Meaningful when ipadUserFilterByVpiVci is enabled. Meaningless when collecting PPP or Frame Relay statistics.

ipadUserVci.name: ipadUserVci
ipadUserVci.description: Specifies the Vci for this user type; identifies a VC when combined with the ipadUserService and ipadUserVpi objects. Meaningful when ipadUserFilterByVpiVci is enabled. Meaningless when collecting PPP or Frame Relay statistics.

ipadUserFilterByVpiVci.name: ipadUserFilterByVpiVci
ipadUserFilterByVpiVci.description: Enables Vpi/Vci filtering for this user statistic. A packet is counted towards the user statistics if the packet is transmitted on the service/Vpi/Vci combindation specified by ipadUserService, ipadUserVpi, and ipadUserVci.

ipadUserIPStatTimeRemaining.name: ipadUserIPStatTimeRemaining
ipadUserIPStatTimeRemaining.description: Specifies seconds until the next IP TopN report is generated.

ipadUserIPStatTimeDuration.name: ipadUserIPStatTimeDuration
ipadUserIPStatTimeDuration.description: The value of TimeRemaining when TimeRemaining was last set. Indicates the number of seconds that the next IP TopN report will cover.

ipadUserIPStatStartTime.name: ipadUserIPStatStartTime
ipadUserIPStatStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime when TimeRemaining was last set.

ipadUserIPStatRequestedReportSize.name: ipadUserIPStatRequestedReportSize
ipadUserIPStatRequestedReportSize.description: Determines the requested maximum number of entries in the topN report.

ipadUserIPStatGrantedReportSize.name: ipadUserIPStatGrantedReportSize
ipadUserIPStatGrantedReportSize.description: Determines the granted number of entries in the topN report. This is by definition less than or equal to requested report size.

ipadUserIPStatReportNumber.name: ipadUserIPStatReportNumber
ipadUserIPStatReportNumber.description: Specifies the number of reports that have been generated. This value resets to zero when the unit is restarted.

ipadUserIPStatDiscardType.name: ipadUserIPStatDiscardType
ipadUserIPStatDiscardType.description: The internal table used to track TopN statistics is finite in size. On the condition when the internal table is full and a new IP address is encountered, an element already existing in the table must be removed. This variable determines the manner of selection. Writing byTime(1) will cause the entry with the least recent frame to be discarded. That is, all other entries in the table will have transmitted or received at least one packet more recently. Writing byFrames(2) will select the entry with the fewest transmitted or received frames. Writing byOctets(3) will select the entry with the fewest transmitted or received octets. The default is byTime(1).

ipadPPPCfgTableEntry.name: ipadPPPCfgTableEntry
ipadPPPCfgTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad PPP configuration table.

ipadPPPCfgService.name: ipadPPPCfgService
ipadPPPCfgService.description: The index into the PPP configuration table; an entry in the ipad service table.

ipadPPPCfgDialMode.name: ipadPPPCfgDialMode
ipadPPPCfgDialMode.description: Determines the permancency of a communications connection.

ipadPPPCfgInactivityTimer.name: ipadPPPCfgInactivityTimer
ipadPPPCfgInactivityTimer.description: Determines when a dial-up or demand-dial connection will be disconnected due to inactivity in both directions. When this parameter is set to zero then the timer is disabled.

ipadPPPCfgNegotiationInit.name: ipadPPPCfgNegotiationInit
ipadPPPCfgNegotiationInit.description: Determines if the port waits for the other end to initiate parameter negotiations.

ipadPPPCfgMRU.name: ipadPPPCfgMRU
ipadPPPCfgMRU.description: The maximum receive unit the interface will accept. Valid values are in the range 128 - 4096, default is 1500.

ipadPPPCfgACCM.name: ipadPPPCfgACCM
ipadPPPCfgACCM.description: Sets the async control character map used when generating async HDLC frames. Setting a bit in the map causes the corresponding character to be mapped for transparency.

ipadPPPCfgNegMRU.name: ipadPPPCfgNegMRU
ipadPPPCfgNegMRU.description: Determines if MRU size is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegMagic.name: ipadPPPCfgNegMagic
ipadPPPCfgNegMagic.description: Determines if the magic number is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegCompression.name: ipadPPPCfgNegCompression
ipadPPPCfgNegCompression.description: Determines if the PPP protocol header compression is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegAddress.name: ipadPPPCfgNegAddress
ipadPPPCfgNegAddress.description: Determines if the PPP HDLC header compression is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegPAP.name: ipadPPPCfgNegPAP
ipadPPPCfgNegPAP.description: Determines if PAP is negotiated with the peer when a more secure authentication protocol is rejected.

ipadPPPCfgNegCHAP.name: ipadPPPCfgNegCHAP
ipadPPPCfgNegCHAP.description: Determines if CHAP is negotiated with the peer when a more secure authentication protocol is rejected.

ipadPPPCfgAllowPAP.name: ipadPPPCfgAllowPAP
ipadPPPCfgAllowPAP.description: Determines if PAP is allowed to be negotiated by the peer.

ipadPPPCfgAllowCHAP.name: ipadPPPCfgAllowCHAP
ipadPPPCfgAllowCHAP.description: Determines if CHAP is allowed to be negotiated by the peer.

ipadPPPCfgPAPUsername.name: ipadPPPCfgPAPUsername
ipadPPPCfgPAPUsername.description: Identification string to determine the user identity.

ipadPPPCfgPAPPassword.name: ipadPPPCfgPAPPassword
ipadPPPCfgPAPPassword.description: Password string to validate the user identity.

ipadPPPCfgCHAPUsername.name: ipadPPPCfgCHAPUsername
ipadPPPCfgCHAPUsername.description: Identification string to determine the user identity.

ipadPPPCfgCHAPSecret.name: ipadPPPCfgCHAPSecret
ipadPPPCfgCHAPSecret.description: Password string to validate the user identity.

ipadPPPCfgPortIpAddress.name: ipadPPPCfgPortIpAddress
ipadPPPCfgPortIpAddress.description: Sets the IP address of the unit's port.

ipadPPPCfgPeerIpAddress.name: ipadPPPCfgPeerIpAddress
ipadPPPCfgPeerIpAddress.description: Sets the IP address of the unit's peer.

ipadPPPCfgNegIpAddress.name: ipadPPPCfgNegIpAddress
ipadPPPCfgNegIpAddress.description: Determines if IP addresses are dynamically negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegIPCPCompression.name: ipadPPPCfgNegIPCPCompression
ipadPPPCfgNegIPCPCompression.description: Determines if Van Jacobson TCPIP header compression is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgEndpoint.name: ipadPPPCfgEndpoint
ipadPPPCfgEndpoint.description: Endpoint name to run PPP over another protocol.

ipadPPPCfgNegIpMask.name: ipadPPPCfgNegIpMask
ipadPPPCfgNegIpMask.description: Determines if the subnet Mask is negotiated.

ipadPPPCfgNegDNSAddress.name: ipadPPPCfgNegDNSAddress
ipadPPPCfgNegDNSAddress.description: Determines if the DNS address is negotiated.

ipadPPPPAPTableEntry.name: ipadPPPPAPTableEntry
ipadPPPPAPTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad PPP PAP table.

ipadPPPPAPTableIndex.name: ipadPPPPAPTableIndex
ipadPPPPAPTableIndex.description: The index into the PPP PAP association table.

ipadPPPPAPTableUsername.name: ipadPPPPAPTableUsername
ipadPPPPAPTableUsername.description: Identification string to identify the user.

ipadPPPPAPTablePassword.name: ipadPPPPAPTablePassword
ipadPPPPAPTablePassword.description: Password string to validate the user identity.

ipadPPPCHAPTableEntry.name: ipadPPPCHAPTableEntry
ipadPPPCHAPTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad PPP CHAP table.

ipadPPPCHAPTableIndex.name: ipadPPPCHAPTableIndex
ipadPPPCHAPTableIndex.description: The index into the PPP CHAP association table.

ipadPPPCHAPTableUsername.name: ipadPPPCHAPTableUsername
ipadPPPCHAPTableUsername.description: Identification string to identify the user.

ipadPPPCHAPTableSecret.name: ipadPPPCHAPTableSecret
ipadPPPCHAPTableSecret.description: Password string to validate the user identity.

ipadModemDialTableEntry.name: ipadModemDialTableEntry
ipadModemDialTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad modem dialing parameters table.

ipadModemDialTableIndex.name: ipadModemDialTableIndex
ipadModemDialTableIndex.description: The index into the ipad modem dialing parameters table. Equivalent to MIB-II ifIndex.

ipadModemDialDataIndex.name: ipadModemDialDataIndex
ipadModemDialDataIndex.description: An index into the Modem Data Table, which selects a modem.

ipadModemDialNumber.name: ipadModemDialNumber
ipadModemDialNumber.description: Specifies the telephone number to dial.

ipadModemDialAbortTimer.name: ipadModemDialAbortTimer
ipadModemDialAbortTimer.description: Aborts a connection attempt if a dial-up connection has failed to connect within the specified number of seconds. Range is 1..255.

ipadModemDialRedialAttempts.name: ipadModemDialRedialAttempts
ipadModemDialRedialAttempts.description: Determines how many attempts to initiate a dial-up connection after the initial failure. Range is 0..10.

ipadModemDialDelayBeforeRedial.name: ipadModemDialDelayBeforeRedial
ipadModemDialDelayBeforeRedial.description: Specifies the number of seconds to wait before redialing. Range is 1..255.

ipadModemDialLoginScript.name: ipadModemDialLoginScript
ipadModemDialLoginScript.description: Script string interpreted after an originated dial-up connection is first established.

ipadModemDialUsername.name: ipadModemDialUsername
ipadModemDialUsername.description: Identification string to determine the user identity.

ipadModemDialPassword.name: ipadModemDialPassword
ipadModemDialPassword.description: Password string to validate the user identity.

ipadModemDialChallengeScript.name: ipadModemDialChallengeScript
ipadModemDialChallengeScript.description: Script string interpreted after an answered dial-up connection is first established.

ipadModemDialAnswerRings.name: ipadModemDialAnswerRings
ipadModemDialAnswerRings.description: Answers an incoming call on the given number of rings. A value of zero disables answering. Range is 0..255.

ipadModemDialCommand.name: ipadModemDialCommand
ipadModemDialCommand.description: The set values perform the following actions: setupNow - Execute the modem setup scripts dialNow - Initiate dialing procedures answerNow - Initiate answering procedures disconnectNow - Initiate disconnect procedures

ipadModemDialStatus.name: ipadModemDialStatus
ipadModemDialStatus.description: This object reports the current activity of the modem control feature disabled - The feature is not enabled setup - The feature is configuring the modem error - The feature could not setup the modem idle - The feature is ready to operate dialing - The feature is placing a call dialWait - The feature is between call attempts ringing - The feature is waiting for an incoming call to connect or go away answering - The feature is answering a call negotiating - The feature is negotiating the login security online - The feature data path is connected disconnecting - The feature is disconnecting a call awaitingCallback - The feature is waiting for a security callback

ipadModemDialSecurity.name: ipadModemDialSecurity
ipadModemDialSecurity.description: disable - Dial-up security not enabled password - Challenge/Login password scripts used callback - Password security followed by answerer calling back callbackVerify - Callback and verify using the callback challenge/response scripts

ipadModemDialCallbackRedialDelay.name: ipadModemDialCallbackRedialDelay
ipadModemDialCallbackRedialDelay.description: Specifies the number of seconds to wait before redialing. Range is 1..255.

ipadModemDialCallbackTimeout.name: ipadModemDialCallbackTimeout
ipadModemDialCallbackTimeout.description: This object sets the number of seconds to wait for a security callback before failing the connection attempt.

ipadModemDialCallbackChalScript.name: ipadModemDialCallbackChalScript
ipadModemDialCallbackChalScript.description: Callback security challenge script interpreted after originating a callback dial-up connection.

ipadModemDialCallbackRspScript.name: ipadModemDialCallbackRspScript
ipadModemDialCallbackRspScript.description: Callback security challenge response script interpreted after answering a callback dial-up connection.

ipadModemDataTableEntry.name: ipadModemDataTableEntry
ipadModemDataTableEntry.description: An entry in the ipad modem database parameters table.

ipadModemDataTableIndex.name: ipadModemDataTableIndex
ipadModemDataTableIndex.description: The index into the ipad modem database parameters table.

ipadModemDataModemName.name: ipadModemDataModemName
ipadModemDataModemName.description: Identification string for the modem database.

ipadModemDataSetupScript.name: ipadModemDataSetupScript
ipadModemDataSetupScript.description: First script interpreted when a modem port is initialized.

ipadModemDataDialingScript.name: ipadModemDataDialingScript
ipadModemDataDialingScript.description: Script interpreted when a dial-up connection is initiated.

ipadModemDataAnswerScript.name: ipadModemDataAnswerScript
ipadModemDataAnswerScript.description: Script interpreted when a modem port decides to answer an incoming call.

ipadModemDataHangupScript.name: ipadModemDataHangupScript
ipadModemDataHangupScript.description: Script interpreted when a dial-up connection is no longer needed.

ipadModemDataSyncScript.name: ipadModemDataSyncScript
